# Frontend navigation state persistence

## Rule: every view-routing state MUST survive a page reload

The user MUST land on the exact same screen after any reload (manual F5,
deploy-triggered auto-reload, browser restart, new tab at the same URL).

---

## What counts as "navigation / view state"

- Which top-level section is active (`activeSection`)
- Which overlay / sheet is open (`activeSheet`)
- Which entity / export is selected
- Which product detail is open
- Products table search string and sort settings
- Advertising date range
- Window scroll position

**Not** navigation state (do not persist):

- Data caches (cost prices, orders matrix, JAM rows — they have their own cache keys)
- Loading / saving / error flags
- Token input text
- UI-only transient state (hover, focus, resize drag)

---

## Where persistence lives

| File | Responsibility |
|------|----------------|
| `persistence/dashboardViewStateTypes.ts` | `DashboardViewState` type, defaults, validators |
| `persistence/dashboardViewSession.ts` | localStorage read/write (key `wb-dashboard-view-state-v2`) |
| `persistence/dashboardViewUrl.ts` | URL param read/write (method + products deep links) |
| `persistence/dashboardViewState.ts` | Public API merging both sources |
| `useDashboardBrowserEffects.ts` | Writes on every state change, restores scroll |

---

## Checklist when adding new navigation state

1. Add the field to `DashboardViewState` in `dashboardViewStateTypes.ts`
2. Add a validator (`isXxx`) in the same file
3. Read and validate the field in `readDashboardViewStateFromSessionStorage` (dashboardViewSession.ts)
4. Write it in `writeDashboardViewStateToSessionStorage`
5. Re-export the type from `dashboardViewState.ts` if used outside persistence/
6. Accept the new field in `useDashboardBrowserEffects` input and add it to the `writeDashboardViewState` call
7. In `WbDashboard.tsx`: initialise `useState` from `persistedViewState.<field>` (not a hardcoded default)
8. Pass the state value to `useDashboardBrowserEffects`

**If you skip any of these 8 steps the state will reset on reload.**

---

## Storage key versioning

The key is `wb-dashboard-view-state-v2` (localStorage).
Bump the suffix (`-v3`, etc.) only when you remove a field or change its
meaning so that stale stored values would cause a broken UI. Adding new
fields with safe defaults does NOT require a key bump.

---

## Sheet / overlay consolidation

All mutually exclusive overlay sheets within `catalog-products` are
represented by a single `activeSheet: ActiveSheet` enum
(`"none" | "cost-price" | "orders" | "jam"`) rather than separate boolean
flags. When adding a new overlay sheet:

- Add its value to `ActiveSheet` union in `dashboardViewStateTypes.ts`
- Add it to the `isActiveSheet` validator
- In `WbDashboard.tsx`, derive the boolean (`const isXxxOpen = activeSection === "catalog-products" && activeSheet === "xxx"`)
- Call `setActiveSheet("xxx")` / `setActiveSheet("none")` in the open/close handlers

Do NOT add new `boolean` sheet flags alongside the `activeSheet` field.
